2. In Private 
14. A Guest House 
“Mendicants, suppose there was a guest house. Lodgers come from the east, west, north, and south. Aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, and workers all stay there. 
In the same way, various feelings arise in this body: pleasant, painful, and neutral feelings. 
Also material pleasant, painful, and neutral feelings arise. 
Also spiritual pleasant, painful, and neutral feelings arise.” 
